The paper deals with the computational complexity of the Matrix Completion problem, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science. However, given the focus on low-rank optimization and the use of combinatorial reductions, it is most likely to be classified under Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), or Computational Geometry (cs.CG).
